- 2 strains of virus. 15 Sep 2015. (reported) The Health Ministry has identified 2 types of Zika virus strains -- one similar to the one in Brazil and Singapore (French Polynesia) and the other a local strain (Micronesia) from an earlier case recorded in the country.

[Interestingly, the genetic analysis from Singapore (report above) indicates that 2 virus isolates were related to an earlier Asian type, not to the South American strain. - Mod.TY]

